net.sf.jclal.activelearning.multilabel.querystrategy

Class MultiLabel3DimensionalQueryStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclal.activelearning.querystrategy.AbstractQueryStrategy
      • net.sf.jclal.activelearning.multilabel.querystrategy.AbstractMultiLabelQueryStrategy
        • net.sf.jclal.activelearning.multilabel.querystrategy.MultiLabel3DimensionalQueryStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IConfigure, IQueryStrategy, JCLAL

    public class MultiLabel3DimensionalQueryStrategy
extends AbstractMultiLabelQueryStrategy
implements IConfigure
    Implementation of 3Dimensional strategy. In this moment only the CMN and CAN strategies are supported. See for more information Esuli, A., and Sebastiani, F. (2009). Active Learning Strategies for Multi-Label Text Classification, 102-113.
    Author:
    Oscar Gabriel Reyes Pupo
    See Also:

      • configure

        public void configure(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration configuration)
        Description copied from interface: IConfigure
        Configuration method.
        Specified by:
        configure in interface IConfigure
        Overrides:
        configure in class AbstractQueryStrategy
        Parameters:
        configuration - The configuration object for MultiLabel3DimensionalQueryStrategy The XML labels supported are:
        • evidence-dimension: The possible values are [C, S]
        • class-dimension: The possible values are [M, A, R]
        • weight-dimension: The possible values are [N, M]
